  "response": "Actually, \"possum\" and \"opossum\" refer to different animals:\n\n1. Opossum (Didelphimorphia):\n- Native to the Americas\n- Marsupial mammals\n- Have a pointed snout, naked tail, and are known for \"playing dead\"\n- Found primarily in North and South America\n\n2. Possum (Phalangeridae):\n- Native to Australia and surrounding regions\n- Also marsupials, but from a different family\n- Typically have furry tails and rounder faces\n- Various species like brushtail possums and ringtail possums\n- Found in Australia, New Guinea, and nearby islands\n\nIn everyday American English, people often use \"possum\" as a shortened version of \"opossum,\" but they are technically different animals from different continents.",
